Hey dude, I'm reading this so far and is starting to touch my curiosity, however...

Your style of writing is confusing me a lot.
My first language its not the english, and maybe I'm not the best to give tips of writing, but reading your story is like throwing words on the google traductor.

Lets start with something easy to spot, like, sometimes I lose the track of who is talking
>Hi agent anon nice to meet you holding out a hand for a handshake

Okay, if you only read this, your brain will give you the message that sheriff is saying this "phrase" to Anon.
But when you keep reading...
>He just stares at anon's hand inhales a long breath

Now you are starting to realize Anon was actually the one saying this to the sheriff
See what I mean? You have to indicate who is talking

A way you can fix this is putting these " " when someone's talk

For example:
>"Hi, agent anon, nice to meet you" said Anon, holding out a hand for a handshake
Another one: >>11306826
>"Hey Doc" Joe takes his hat off

(Also, I forgot to mention this, you have to use more commas to not make a salad of words.)
See now how big is the difference with putting " " and some commas?

I saw more mistakes like this and others on your story and I hope some writefriends here can give you tips about greens, (Like I said, I'm not one, and my english is very limited, even this post surely have some grammar issues)
